14 SECTION 4. IC 25-1-9-24 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
15 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
16 1, 2026]: Sec. 24. (a) This section applies to a practitioner who
17 conducts well-child visits.
18 (b) At each well-child visit, a practitioner may do the following:
19 (1) Ask the child's parent or guardian about firearm safety,
20 including whether:
21 (A) there is a firearm in the home; and
22 (B) if there is a firearm in the home, it is stored safely.
23 (2) Provide information or resources to the child's parent or
24 guardian on secure firearm storage practices.
25 (c) Any conversation described in subsection (b)(1) is considered
26 the standard of care and is confidential.
